ClientSideRequests.name: ClientSideRequests
ClientSideRequests.description:
Shared functions which construct "endpoint strings" for API requests.
For examle: loan(id) returns "loan/{id}" 
Purpose: If we ever change the URL schema of our NodeJS server, we only need to update the URLs in this one file

CVNumberLine.name: CVNumberLine
CVNumberLine.description: Creates a number line with a value enclose in a circle

Loan.name: Loan
Loan.description:
Loan is meant to be shared between server and client side code
 It's properties match those in the GraphQL scheme (insofar as possible)
It's constructor takes no arguments. All properties must be set with the
 results of a GraphQL API call/MongoDB call.
However: Note that contained objects, like 'geocode' or 'image' that have
 their own types in the GraphQL API do not have their own types here. They
 are simply treated as vanilla JSON objects

 For example: Get loan by id, Update loan to say user 34 already reviewed

Secondary: If true (or merely defined like <button secondary>), uses the secondary button style (white background, green border, green text)

Font Size: Allows the font size to be overridden (X pixels). Otherwise, we use the size defined in CVButton.css
Horizontal Padding: Allows the horizontal padding of the text to be overridden. Otherwise, there is no explicit padding define (except a min-width of 320px)

  1. string? title: an optional table title

  Interface: CVPage
 
 
     All pages we create (ReviewPage, EvaluationResultsPage, etc) must implement
     all the methods in this interface.
 
      This is not to be confused with the <Page> component, which actually renders
      ReviewPage/EvaluationResultsPage components.
 
      This interface exists to enforce standard on all pages we build.
 
 State: None
 Props: None

Callback when page loads. This is your chance to fetch data before constructing your page view

REQURIED IMPLEMENTATION IN SUBCLASS
Return a page lead (see /src/leads/) matching this page's purpose (Ex: ProfileLead)

OPTIONAL IMPLEMENTION IN SUBCLASS
If the function is set to return true, the page
will rerender when the user object is fully loaded

OPTIONAL IMPLEMENTION IN SUBCLASS
If, for any reason this page should redirect
before loading, implement that here with window.location.href = ...

classitems.name: graphph Requests data from the Kiva GraphQL

params.name: query
params.description: JSX query in the form of a string (use tick (`) character for a multiline string)

classitems.name: csv "Search CSV files for some info"

params.name: search
params.description: Array of search targets. Properties for each object shown below

params.name: search[i].label
params.description: Label for this value in the resulting associative array

params.name: search[i].file
params.description: File path to CSV file

params.name: search[i].property
params.description: Index of the property to get

params.name: search[i].key
params.description: Will be matched exactly to the primary key of a row

params.name: search[i].keyindex
params.description: What row index is the primary key on

params.name: file
params.description: All requests will be made to the same on the same CSV file

params.name: key
params.description: All requests will be requesting for the same key

params.name: keyindex
params.description:
All requests will be made using the same keyindex (usually used in conjunction with the "key" param)
 [
   { 
     label: '<label for this value in the resulting associative array>'
     file: '<file name>'
     property: <column index>
     key: <match Loan name>
     keyindex: <column index of the name>
     multiple: if true, will return multiple results as array
   }
 ]

throws.description: Common error: Results for a key are 0 or > 1.

classitems.description: Gets the row for a project with the given name in the given CSV file

params.name: file
params.description: Path to CSV file

params.name: key
params.description: Match this search key (will be matched used javascript == operator)

params.name: keyindex
params.description: What index is the primary key in?

params.name: customComparator
params.description: (Optionally) Instead of using JavaScript == to compare keys, use this function (value, key) -> Bool. This could be useful in using case insensitive comparators, checking just if the first word is equal, etc. This is optional.

return.description: A (nullable) array of values (a single row from the CSV file)
